<sec id="id-d86ecf81-1056-4d4e-c271-bfa80b3f8cc4"><title><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="d2622743-8875-41f0-e1b4-3faf06db962d" timestamp="1627509549816"?>Records destruction<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d2622743-8875-41f0-e1b4-3faf06db962d"?></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="4b9c7bdf-bab1-4a3b-d37a-5aa4ac8a5318" timestamp="1627509613235"?>A key privacy protection requirement is that of the mandatory destruction, i.e. as the reverse of records retention. Within an information/records management and archiving context this is known as "disposition". Disposition is an authorized action to remove, i.e., alienate, a set of recorded information, from under the control of a Person and thereby extinguishing ownership and accountability.<xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-f7d393aa-dd27-4779-aede-ab5d3a7b9682.xml#id-9e0ab3fd-5f11-430b-8cca-76fb10f6a3c3" id="id-b6fcbc9a-723c-42c0-a09e-97b77f69b299" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><fn id="id-9e0ab3fd-5f11-430b-8cca-76fb10f6a3c3"><p>This is more than “erasing” or “deleting” an SRI in an IT system. From an “evidentiary” requirements perspective, the requirement here is that of “expungement” (= eliminate completely, wipe out, destroy or obliterate an electronic record).</p></fn> In the context of this standard, “Open-edi disposition” is defined as:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4b9c7bdf-bab1-4a3b-d37a-5aa4ac8a5318"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="4c95c235-8047-4608-883d-481bfc3d7e98" timestamp="1627509581853"?><bold><italic>Open-edi disposition</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4c95c235-8047-4608-883d-481bfc3d7e98"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="5ea0c111-f2c2-474d-8195-67b13bcd37bc" timestamp="1627509581853"?><bold><italic>process</italic></bold> <italic>governing the implementation of formally approved records retention, destruction (or expungement) or transfer of <bold>recorded information</bold> under the control of a <bold>Person</bold> which are documented in disposition authorities or similar instruments</italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5ea0c111-f2c2-474d-8195-67b13bcd37bc"?></p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="4eb00332-1bc2-45ee-ebc0-44c04fc2d3d7" timestamp="1627775875161"?><non-normative-note><p><italic>Adapted from ISO 15489-1.</italic></p></non-normative-note><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4eb00332-1bc2-45ee-ebc0-44c04fc2d3d7"?><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7fb1102a-b6d2-409e-88cb-2aa85986b9ba" timestamp="1627509581853"?>[ISO/IEC 15944-5:2014, 3.90]<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7fb1102a-b6d2-409e-88cb-2aa85986b9ba"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7f3d09df-33fe-448e-da98-f95a6223ae00" timestamp="1627509581853"?>There are basically a limited number of disposal actions. These are identified in the following coded domain 03 found in ISO/IEC15944-8.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7f3d09df-33fe-448e-da98-f95a6223ae00"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="2fe9aea9-8c9d-4ad4-f877-60ec03efb987" timestamp="1627509581853"?><bold>Rule D-009:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2fe9aea9-8c9d-4ad4-f877-60ec03efb987"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="3c33efb5-c39f-4956-e130-6fe933a42c05" timestamp="1627509581853"?><bold>Where an individual participates in the role of an individual learner to a learning transaction, the LET provider shall specify the disposition action to be taken at the end of the expiry of the record retention period in accordance with privacy protection requirements of the applicable jurisdictional domain.</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="3c33efb5-c39f-4956-e130-6fe933a42c05"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6a079178-809f-4661-9a79-3b308636ce72" timestamp="1627509581852"?><bold><italic>Guideline D-009G1:</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6a079178-809f-4661-9a79-3b308636ce72"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="e9e4f3f4-37ef-4b2b-f4c6-bbd12ce28032" timestamp="1627509581852"?><bold><italic>In support of Rule D-007, the LET provider as well as any other parties to the learning transaction, (e.g., a regulator, an agent, and/or third party) should use the ISO/IEC 15944-5 Coded Domain 03 “Codes representing disposition of recorded information” as and where applicable.</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e9e4f3f4-37ef-4b2b-f4c6-bbd12ce28032"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="066be741-3ce9-4c7a-eb08-3987e3c01d7f" timestamp="1627509581852"?><bold><italic>Guideline D-009G2:</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="066be741-3ce9-4c7a-eb08-3987e3c01d7f"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="df5762f8-1310-4a48-8b98-7f215ec8173b" timestamp="1627509581852"?><bold><italic>It is a recommended best practice for a LET provider to inform the individual learner that it by law or best practice will retain specified SRIs on the individual learner as long as that organization exists, (e.g., the fact that the individual learner “graduated” at whatever level of accomplishment).</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="df5762f8-1310-4a48-8b98-7f215ec8173b"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="84dd6294-f99d-4678-a85a-91194637a5de" timestamp="1627775935890"?>It is reproduced here below as <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-f7d393aa-dd27-4779-aede-ab5d3a7b9682.xml#id-9d3a80c3-d295-46e1-a940-7e35eedd829e" ref-type="table" id="id-d677ed43-fcb3-40d5-c6ac-ea70d80a986e" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="84dd6294-f99d-4678-a85a-91194637a5de"?></p><table-wrap id="id-9d3a80c3-d295-46e1-a940-7e35eedd829e"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7eb79093-ab8b-4609-dad2-918779328648" timestamp="1627775900450"?><caption><title>ISO/IEC 15944-5:03 Codes representing disposition of recorded information<sup><xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-f7d393aa-dd27-4779-aede-ab5d3a7b9682.xml#id-8c9a7aaf-4fad-43d0-a68a-697edc8b5ef3" id="id-c13cfd52-cc73-4388-e787-205ca0817a22" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref></sup></title></caption><table><col width="20%"/><col width="20%"/><col width="20%"/><col width="20%"/><col width="20%"/><tbody><tr><td colspan="5" align="center" valign="top"><p><bold>ISO/IEC 15944-5:03 Codes representing disposition of recorded information</bold></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" align="center" valign="top"><p><bold>IT Interface</bold></p></td><td colspan="2" align="center" valign="top"><p><bold>Human Interface Equivalent: Linguistic – Written Form</bold></p></td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top"><p><bold>Source Authority ID</bold></p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p><bold>Coded Domain ID</bold></p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p><bold>ID</bold></p><p><bold>Code</bold></p></td><td valign="top"><p><bold>ISO English</bold></p></td><td valign="top"><p><bold>ISO French</bold></p></td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top"><p>15944-5</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>03</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>00</p></td><td valign="top"><p>Other</p></td><td valign="top"><p>autre</p></td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top"><p>15944-5</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>03</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>01</p></td><td valign="top"><p>destruction or expungement</p></td><td valign="top"/></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top"><p>15944-5</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>03</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>02</p></td><td valign="top"><p>transfer to another organization</p></td><td valign="top"/></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top"><p>15944-5</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>03</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>03</p></td><td valign="top"><p>transfer to an archive (for historical and research purposes)</p></td><td valign="top"/></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top"><p>15944-5</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>03</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>04</p></td><td align="left" valign="top"><p>do not destroy, maintain and conserve as a permanent SRI</p></td><td valign="top"/></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top"><p>15944-5</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>03</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>98</p></td><td valign="top"><p>not known</p></td><td valign="top"><p>inconnu</p></td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top"><p>15944-5</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>03</p></td><td align="center" valign="top"><p>99</p></td><td valign="top"><p>not applicable<xref ref-type="table-fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-f7d393aa-dd27-4779-aede-ab5d3a7b9682.xml#id-d3b4cd80-77f1-43ad-c4c2-a66e1adaf225" id="id-1b7c4615-5200-40b2-cdae-a2db10d87cd0" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref></p></td><td valign="top"><p>sans objet</p></td></tr></tbody></table><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7eb79093-ab8b-4609-dad2-918779328648"?><table-wrap-foot><fn id="id-d3b4cd80-77f1-43ad-c4c2-a66e1adaf225"><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="c90cf546-ed83-49f5-bccd-cac1b8d4d338" timestamp="1627509657764"?>This would apply to recorded information deemed to be transitory or ephemeral which can be discarded anytime.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="c90cf546-ed83-49f5-bccd-cac1b8d4d338"?></p></fn></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap><p/></sec>
